ctrl-u delete the line
ctrl-a move to the aaa
ctrl-e move to the end
ctrl-w delete the last argument
ctrl-r search the used command
ctrl-b move by word -before-
ctrl-f move by word -after- 
alt-.. pop the prior last args
history list the prior commands
!! indicate the last command
!$ indicate the last argument
!n indicate the last command-argument combination
~ indicate the home directory
/ indicate the root directory
- indicate the last directory
alt-# make current line a comment line so that you can return it by history later
column -t ** make each line align correctly
less ctrl-b ctrl-f gg G the use is the same as vim
